comments.body:
## ⚠️ Code Issue

**Lines:** 328-328

```cpp
                                   /*bypass_limits=*/false, /*test_accept=*/!single_submit));
```

This code snippet hardcodes the `bypass_limits` parameter to `false`. In a fuzzing context, this parameter should ideally be controlled by the fuzzer's input to explore a wider range of test cases, including those that bypass limits. This limitation reduces the effectiveness of the fuzz test in uncovering potential bugs related to limit enforcement.

